FT  22 DEC 94 / International Company News: Airgas makes offer for
industrial gas unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Airgas, a Delaware-based gas distribution company, has made an unsolicited
offer for the industrial gas business of CBI Industries, valuing the unit at
Dollars 680m, writes Richard Waters. Airgas also offered to take on all of
CBI's debt, which amounts to a further Dollars 770m.
CBI dismissed the offer as 'inadequate' and said it had no intention of
selling the unit, which raised the prospect of a bidding war for the whole
company and pushed up its shares when the offer emerged on Tuesday.
