</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Salomon Brothers is losing another top executive to Long Term Capital
Management, the specialist money-management company set up by the Wall
Street securities firm's former vice-chairman, Mr John Meriwether, writes
Patrick Harverson.
Yesterday, Mr Hans Hufschmid, head of Salomon's worldwide foreign exchange
operations, announced his resignation from the firm. He is expected to join
LTCM shortly, where he will become the latest in a line of top personnel to
have left Salomon for Mr Meriwether's operation, which is based in the New
York suburb of Greenwich, Connecticut.
