Mr Brian North, chairman, said that in the six months to October 31 lower
sales in the video games market had reduced turnover in Masterpack's
contract packaging business by Pounds 1m. Group sales fell to Pounds 4.66m
(Pounds 4.88m).
The interim dividend is cut to 1p (2.5p) and the group expects to repeat
this payment in the second half. Earnings per share were 1.33p (6.56p).
