FT  22 DEC 94 / Pension schemes shift holdings
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK pension schemes were unusually heavy sellers of shares in foreign
companies in the third quarter, data from the Central Statistics Office
show.
Pension schemes sold Pounds 1.9bn of foreign shares in the quarter,
continuing a trend started in the second quarter when their holdings fell by
a net Pounds 694m. The outflow from foreign shares was greater in the third
quarter than the total net inflow by pension schemes for the whole of last
year.
