<HEADLINE>
FT  22 DEC 94 / TUC underwrites union's overdraft
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Trades Union Congress general council agreed yesterday to underwrite a
Pounds 250,000 extension to the Pounds 1.2m overdraft facility held by
Ucatt, the construction union, with Unity Trust Bank.
The TUC's move is unprecedented but Mr John Monks, general secretary, said
yesterday that no UK trade union in had ever gone bankrupt. Mr Doug Douglas,
deposed as president of the GPMU print union by its executive, has won his
case in the High Court and been reinstated. The union will not appeal.
</TEXT>
