<HEADLINE>
FT  22 DEC 94 / Monks urges curbs on top pay rises
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Trade union trustees of corporate pension funds have been urged to support
action to curb excessive executive pay rises in companies in which their
funds have shares.
Mr John Monks, Trades Union Congress general secretary, has written to 1,000
trustees calling for their inclusion in company remuneration committees. He
said executive pay should be related to workforce pay in general.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
