FT  22 DEC 94 / World Trade News: Statoil recommends laying new gas pipeline
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   OSLO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Norway's state oil company Statoil said it recommended laying a new gas
pipeline to Dunkirk in France from the North Seaat an estimated cost of
SKr9bn (Dollars 1.2bn). The recommendation has to be approved by the gas
supply committee and parliament.
</TEXT>
