<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Herve de Charette, France's housing minister, yesterday warned Mr Jacques
Chirac, mayor of Paris and presidential candidate, that his call for
compulsory requisitioning of vacant houses and flats for the capital's
homeless would deter property investment. Instead he proposed to Prime
Minister Edouard Balladur that the government pay special premiums to get
