poor with rent. To dramatise the plight of the homeless at Christmas, the
venerable Abbe Pierre, long-time champion of France's homeless, last weekend
led a squat of a company-owned property in a smart Paris district, a move
promptly exploited by Mr Chirac and his presidential rival, Mr Balladur.
