FT  21 DEC 94 / International Company News: ConAgra sees further growth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   OMAHA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ConAgra, the US diversified foods group, said it expects fiscal 1995 to be
its 15th consecutive year of record earnings, Reuter reports from Omaha.
Mr Philip Fletcher, chairman, said: 'We believe it also will be a year in
which ConAgra creates substantial shareholder value for the future.'
Net income for the second quarter ended November 27 was Dollars 0.63 a
share, up from Dollars 0.56 a year ago. In the first half, ConAgra earned
Dollars 0.94 a share, up from Dollars 0.83. 'Our company's first-half
results were excellent, but our actions to drive future results were more
important,' Mr Fletcher said.
He said ConAgra had acquired several businesses that fit tightly with core
operations and add quickly to earnings. It began an accelerated programme to
divest non-core businesses and continued to refresh branded foods, including
Healthy Choice, he added.
