FT  21 DEC 94 / International Company News: Bankers Trust warns on profits
for quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Bankers Trust yesterday became the third big New York-based bank in a week
to issue a profits warning, underlining the damage to the revenues of some
banks caused by the weakness in financial markets.
The bank, which relies more heavily than many competitors on income from
trading in financial markets, said earnings in the final three months of
this year were likely to be below the Dollars 169m after-tax profits of the
third quarter.
It blamed the fall on 'persistently difficult market conditions and a
resulting decline in client activity'.
At the same time, the bank said it was raising its quarterly dividend to
Dollars 1 a share from 90 cents, reflecting long-term growth prospects.
In this, Bankers Trust mirrored J. P. Morgan, which also raised its dividend
last week while warning that profits in the final period would not match the
previous three months.
Meanwhile, Bankers Trust has agreed to cancel two foreign currency
derivative contracts sold to a customer in the US. The customer, Federal
Paper, said it was planning to take a Dollars 12m pre-tax gain in the
current quarter following the cancellation of the two contracts.
</TEXT>
