<TEXT>
Bankers Trust, the US bank which recently bowed to regulators over some
parts of its derivatives activities, has agreed to cancel two foreign
currency derivative contracts sold to a customer in the US.
The customer, Federal Paper, said it was planning to take a Dollars 12m
pre-tax gain in the current quarter following the cancellation of the two
contracts.
It had earlier reported pre-tax losses of Dollars 19m on the contracts,
