<HEADLINE>
FT  21 DEC 94 / Ministers retreat on Companies House sell-off
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JIM KELLY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The government yesterday stepped back from the wholesale privatisation of
Companies House, the official repository of corporate information, but will
go ahead with a programme of contracting out specific services, Jim Kelly
writes.
Companies House is based in Cardiff and has five regional offices. Last year
it handled the incorporation of more than 100,000 new companies. It holds
details on nearly 1m companies.
Mr Michael Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, said in a written
parliamentary answer that it would remain an executive agency of the
government. Last week it was announced that the Patent Office would remain
in the public sector.
Mr Heseltine said that SRU, a private consultancy, had been appointed in
July this year 'to explore further with the market how best to contract out
most of the services of Companies House'.
</TEXT>
