<HEADLINE>
FT  21 DEC 94 / Pepsi wins injunction
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PepsiCo won an unusual court injunction in the US yesterday, preventing a
former senior executive from divulging information about the company to its
rival Quaker Oats.
Mr William Redmond, a general manager of Pepsi's beverages division before
he left in mid-November, has also been barred by the federal court from
taking any part in decisions about the pricing, marketing and distribution
of soft drinks at Quaker for the next six months.
Pepsi said it held no evidence that Mr Redmond had divulged commercially
sensitive information, but the company claimed that his having worked on
PepsiCo's planning and strategy meant he was in possession of highly
sensitive information.
